HEADWORD: Woolfell
<hw>Wool"fell`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Wool</ets> +
<ets>fell</ets> a skin.]</ety> <def>A skin with the wool; a skin from
which the wool has not been sheared or pulled.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>woolfel</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

